OmniScripts Date/Time Element

Enable users to select a date from a date picker and a time from a list by adding the Date/Time element to your OmniScript. Set the minimum and maximum dates, and the date and time formats.

Drag a Text element from the Build panel onto the canvas.
In the Properties panel, give the element a name in the Name field.
In Field Label, enter a label visible to the user.
In Minimum Date, enter the earliest date the user can select from the date picker.
In Maximum Date, enter the latest date the user can select from the date picker.
In Date Format, enter the format to display the date.
In Time Format, enter the format to display the time, such as hh:mm a.
In Time Interval, enter the intervals within an hour the user can select from the time dropdown.

Select Local Timezone or User Timezone for the Time Zone. 

You can also configure additional properties in the Advanced Options section and see Common OmniScript Element Properties Definitions for more information.
title: Configuring OmniScripts Date/Time Element
